<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-03-11T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-03-11T05:00:00-05:00" n="608" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d608">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A 4e/11: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-03-11T18:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">March 11,
                                        1922—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received March 14—12
                                noon.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>98. Your 44, February 25, 3 p.m.<note n="88" xml:id="d608fn88">Not
                                printed.</note> communicated to the Chinese Government. Foreign
                            Office circular note dated 10th to different Legations announces that
                            Chinese Government has appointed its delegates for effective 5 percent
                            revision and has set March 31st at Shanghai for opening of conference.
                            Note requests immediate appointment of delegates and notification of
                            names.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>